cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for semantic image segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces structural priors to improve the training process, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The optimization of the number of filters in each layer of the architecture also suggests a possible connection to neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the experiments performed on image datasets suggest a connection to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
